Japanese manga readability rules:
- Reading flow must follow standard Japanese manga conventions:
  - from right to left
  - from top to bottom
  - from the upper right toward the lower left
- Panel arrangement on both odd pages (right pages) and even pages (left pages) should guide the eye naturally from right to left
- Around 5 to 7 panels per page is a good readability guideline, but adjust when necessary for clarity
- Vertical spacing between panels should be relatively narrow
- Horizontal spacing between panels should be relatively wider so the eye does not get confused
- Diagonal panels may be used effectively for tension, unease, or action scenes, but should not be overused
- Bleed panels / tachikiri panels may be used to create impact, scale, or immersion
- Use character gazes, body movement, object motion, and composition flow to guide the reader’s eye smoothly into the next panel
- The paneling should be readable first, stylish second

